=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Klank_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 833 Hz, featuring punchy attack and impulsive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: impulsive
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 833.0097
  harmonic_decay_rate: -8.3697
  harmonic_regularity: 0.3267
  pitch_clarity: 24.8688
  inharmonicity: 0.5165
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -13.3599
  resonance_freq: 925.9277

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Klank Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Klank.html
// Tags: Klank, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
(
play({
    Klank.ar(`[
        Array.rand(12, 800.0, 4000.0),         // frequencies
        nil,                             // amplitudes (default to 1.0)
        Array.rand(12, 0.1, 2)                // ring times
        ], Decay.ar(Impulse.ar(4), 0.03, ClipNoise.ar(0.01)))
})
)
